## Production Reference: OpenClaude Bundled Cores
OpenClaude ships ~18 bundled cores as battle-tested implementations:

| Core | Trigger | Pattern | CEX Equivalent |
|-------|---------|---------|----------------|
| /simplify | slash_command | 3-parallel-agent review | p04_core_simplify |
| /verify | slash_command | adversarial verification | p04_core_verify |
| /compact | agent_invoked | 9-section summarization | p04_core_compact |
| /loop | slash, agent_invoked | recurring cron schedule | p04_core_loop (future) |
| /stuck | slash_command | diagnostic investigation | n/a (Anthropic-specific) |

**Key architectural insight**: Cores are defined as prompt text with frontmatter, not as code. The core body IS the prompt injected when the core triggers. This maps directly to CEX's core-as-artifact model.

**Parallel execution pattern** (from /simplify):
- Phase 1: Identify changes (git diff)
- Phase 2: Dispatch 3 agents concurrently, each with the full diff + specialized focus
- Phase 3: Aggregate findings and fix issues directly
This pattern generalizes: any core can dispatch parallel sub-agents with typed foci.

**Analysis scratchpad pattern** (from /compact):
- <analysis> tags create a private drafting space
- Forces structured thinking before output
- Scratchpad is stripped from final result
- Improves quality without consuming permanent context

